.TH BUNPY-RUN 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy-run \- run a Python script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy run
.I file.py
[\fIargs...\fR]
.br
.B bunpy
.I file.py
[\fIargs...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs the named Python script through gocopy (compile) and goipy
(bytecode VM). The bare positional form
.B bunpy file.py
is equivalent to
.BR "bunpy run file.py" .
.PP
The script must end in
.IR .py .
Reading from standard input
.RB ( "bunpy run \-" )
is reserved for a later release.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I file.py
Path to the script to run. Must end in
.IR .py .
.TP
.I args...
Forwarded to the script through
.BR sys.argv .
.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero on success. Non-zero if the file cannot be opened, fails to
compile, or raises an uncaught exception. A
.B SystemExit
with an integer code propagates that code.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy (1).
